    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but when you say the evidence is mixed, aren't the statistical studies showing a link between laws and less crime basically more \"concrete\" than the argument about the 2nd amendment? the constitutional stuff feels more like a legal interpretation or an opinion, whereas the crime stats are actual data, right?",
